  {body: "Pikachu pika pika pikachu. Pika pi. Pika pikachu. Pika pika!", author: "Pikachu", score: 4, user_id: 4, commentable_id: 12572, commentable_type: "Game"},
  {body: "Brawl was a stumble in the smash bros franchise, and the 3ds felt like a demo, but the full HD release of Smash Bros Wii U is everything I could have wanted from a smash bros game. The game play is very similar to smash, albeit a little slower paced. Competitive game play is no longer dependent on techniques such as wavedashing, and I feel that it lowers the entry barrier, but still maintains its potential for higher level play. I was a huge melee fan, until I bought this game. I'll probably never see Roy again, but at least mewtwo is coming back!", author: "Sonic", score: 5, user_id: 9, commentable_id: 35573, commentable_type: "Game"},
  {body: "\r\nI've been playing this game for a while, and no, it's not just a mod. The graphics are a bit low poly, but when 10 people are fighting each other onscreen at once with lots of particle effects you don't want to be chug because of the trees, terrain, or mobs being too high res.\r\n\r\nThe game runs very smooth and that's what counts with a PvP game or a MOBA.\r\n\r\nThere are tons of champions to choose from and half the fun is learning all of them. I highly recommend this one.", author: "Sonic", score: 4, user_id: 9, commentable_id: 24024, commentable_type: "Game"},
  {body: "The best most successful game in the MOBA genre. Dominating all others in Esports and players per day it is definitely not a business as you can take it or leave it on the skins and early char unlocks. The support is fantastic and they are constantly evolving the game to keep it relevant and competitive. Any negative comments are from Dota players or people who did not play the game long enough to know what they are talking about. They even sponser multiple gaming communities to dish out thousands of RP per day in low end amateur tourneys based on player skill level. RP is their \"in game money\" for skins.", author: "Peach", score: 3, user_id: 11, commentable_id: 24024, commentable_type: "Game"},
  {body: "Amazing game, may even be the first time a smash game gets a goty award as it is filled with content a ton of new modes and characters( 8 player smash is awesome) and stages. It is truly a next gen game.\r\nI think everyone knew this would be hit with awesome review scores however the real test is how much it helps the wii u, and I hope it helps it a lot", author: "Peach", score: 4, user_id: 11, commentable_id: 35573, commentable_type: "Game"},
  {body: "This game is great the 1st exclusive on ps4 you must buy it if you played and loves demon's souls and dark souls I'm Certain you love this legend .\r\nIf you have or want to buy ps4 you must buy this game.", author: "Peach", score: 3, user_id: 11, commentable_id: 46569, commentable_type: "Game"},
  {body: "There's only 16 maps in the game currently, and Assault isn't one of them, which is kinda like making a Mario game and leaving out Luigi. Matchmaking is another huge problem in this game. I often party up with 4-6 people (to noobstomp ofc) and matchmaking always tries to join full servers or servers with inadequate slots for our party. Then we always have to remake and this happens all the time. CS1.6 is still better than GO atm, but GO is definitely a step up from Source. Valve has a long way to go if they want to make it a classic because this game still feels like a beta.", author: "Peach", score: 1, user_id: 11, commentable_id: 36113, commentable_type: "Game"},
  {body: "This game is the worst of gta world I never thought that this would be the worst of all gta, it's a completely a spend of money well, everyone does with his money what he pleases", author: "Peach", score: 1, user_id: 11, commentable_id: 36765, commentable_type: "Game"},
  {body: "Very awesome game, reminds me of Red Dead Redemption, Skyrim, and Dragon Age. Bringing the best of those together in a world bigger than GTA V is truly something magnificent. While also telling a very good and mature story in a beautiful setting. Ladies and Gentlemen... Let me present The Witcher 3: Wild Hunt. Say goodbye to life for a while! ", author: "Peach", score: 5, user_id: 11, commentable_id: 41484, commentable_type: "Game"},
  {body: "Rocksteady Studios leaves Batman behind at the top of their game in terms of visual presentation, gameplay, and storytelling. While Arkham Knight's innovations are few, they are impactful and smart, and all work towards the common goal of giving the player the ultimate power fantasy of being the Batman. ", author: "Peach", score: 4, user_id: 11, commentable_id: 45577, commentable_type: "Game"},
  {body: "Nintendo splatters the TPS genre with its fresher, smoother and most addictive online experience since Mario Kart, hampered by its lack of content at its launch date. An \"inkcuestionable\" reason to have a Wii U that proves why shooters needed a coat of paint. ", author: "Peach", score: 5, user_id: 11, commentable_id: 46582, commentable_type: "Game"},
  {body: "A game so narrative driven as this would not be effective if the supporting aesthetics aren't up to scratch, and Life Is Strange is nothing short of a gorgeous game. ", author: "Peach", score: 4, user_id: 11, commentable_id: 47342, commentable_type: "Game"},
  {body: "The Old Blood feels like two Wolfenstein games mushed together. The first half of the game is really good, but the enjoyment is truly lacking during the second half, when you’re fighting against bullet-sponge-y enemies and endlessly spawning zombies.", author: "Peach", score: 3, user_id: 11, commentable_id: 49073, commentable_type: "Game"},
  {body: "The bottom line is that this is Mario hop-n-bop action at its finest, with a goodly amount of minigames thrown into the mix for good measure", author: "Peach", score: 5, user_id: 11, commentable_id: 10299, commentable_type: "Game"},
  {body: "It may lack some of the community niceties, beloved maps (Assault, anyone?), and little features of past games, but Global Offensive delivers on the promise of a faithful, polished, and better looking Counter-Strike for whoever wants it. Even if the community doesn't meet the golden standard of 1.6 and Source, CS:GO will remain a multiplayer classic for those willing to put in the time to learn the maps and weapons. ", author: "Lara Croft", score: 5, user_id: 6, commentable_id: 36113, commentable_type: "Game"},
  {body: "Bloodborne takes the best of Dark Souls and builds the unrelenting gaming challenge on a prefect foundation - it will test your abilities to the max. The first true must-have exclusive for PS4 is here.", author: "Lara Croft", score: 5, user_id: 6, commentable_id: 46569, commentable_type: "Game"},
  {body: "It's everything I wanted it to be, and Melee's true successor.", author: "Lara Croft", score: 4, user_id: 6, commentable_id: 35573, commentable_type: "Game"},
  {body: "Wolfenstein: The Old Blood is a short but intense experience that happily blends the innovation of The New Order with the tradition of Return of Castle Wolfenstein. ", author: "Lara Croft", score: 4, user_id: 6, commentable_id: 49073, commentable_type: "Game"},
  {body: "There's enough ground work laid here to pave the way for future installments, but a lot of the good is undone by lip sync issues and some of the most mind-bogglingly bad dialogue that we've heard in recent memory. ", author: "Lara Croft", score: 1, user_id: 6, commentable_id: 47342, commentable_type: "Game"},
